\f0\b\fs90 \cf0 Basic Butter Cookies
\b0\fs52 \
Yield:  6 to 7 dozen cookies
\fs46 \
\

\b\fs62 INGREDIENTS
\b0 \
2 cups {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/flour/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 all-purpose flour}} \
1/2 teaspoon baking powder \
1/2 teaspoon salt \
1 1/2 sticks (3/4 cup) unsalted butter, softened \
1 cup sugar \
1 large {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/eggs/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 egg}} \
1/2 teaspoon {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/extracts/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 vanilla extract}} \

\fs56 \

\b\fs62 DIRECTIONS
\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/whisk/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 Whisk}} together flour, baking powder, and salt in a small bowl. \
Beat together butter and sugar in a large bowl with an electric {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mixer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 mixer}} at medium-high speed until pale and fluffy, about 3 minutes in a standing mixer (preferably fitted with paddle attachment) or 6 with a handheld. Beat in egg and vanilla. Reduce speed to low, then add flour mixture and mix until just combined.\
Form dough into 2 balls and flatten each into a 6-inch disk. Chill disks, wrapped in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/plastic-wrap/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 plastic wrap}}, until firm, at least 1 hour.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs28 \cf0 \

\fs62 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.\
While oven preheats, roll out 1 piece of dough (keep remaining dough chilled) into a 9-inch round (slightly less than 1/4-inch thick) on a well-floured surface with a well-floured {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/rolling-pin/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 rolling pin}}. (If dough becomes too soft to roll out, chill on a baking sheet until firm.) Cut out as many cookies as possible with cutter. \
Bake {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cookie/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 cookies}}, switching position of sheets halfway through baking, until edges are golden, 8 to 10 minutes. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/dredge/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 Dredge}} warm cookies in confectioners' sugar until coated and transfer to a rack to cool completely.\
